subject: Re: [junit] Artifacts deployed to maven 2 central repository
msgSnippet: ... The last couple of JUnit releases have been submitted for upload through JIRA: * http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MAVENUPLOAD-1450 *
messageBody:
On 6/22/07, Stephen Pack <StephenJPack@...> wrote:
>
> I had some trouble resolving the latest version of JUnit from the
> central repository. Brief investigation revealed that it is due to the
> metadata not being properly updated to include the new versions [1],
> although 4.3 and 4.3.1 are hosted there.

The last couple of JUnit releases have been submitted for upload
through JIRA:
* http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MAVENUPLOAD-1450
* http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MAVENUPLOAD-1431

To get the metadata fixed, open a Maven Evangelism issue similar to
this one (which was also for JUnit...):
* http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MEV-370

I'm not sure if something was missed in the upload bundle or if it was
just an oversight.

--
Wendy
